
Pending proper doc, here are somethings to make sure we eventually document:

The expected sequence of:

  mu_rtc_set_alarm_cb(foo)
  mu_rtc_set_alarm(t)

Suggests that we should document those functions which aren't interrupt safe.  For example, mu_rtc_set_alarm_cb is non-atomic since function pointers are bigger than 8 bits.   This means that calling mu_rtc_set_alarm_cb() when there is a pending alarm (match) set is unsafe.   

What about the use case in which the callback sets the next alarm time (at which point it will be called again and set yet another alarm etc)?

